## Atomic Design Hierarchy

### Atoms (primitives)

- **Frame** (`components/Frame/Frame.tsx`): Post-neobrutalist bordered container. A self-contained piece of UI or content. Thick black borders (4px default). Selective rounded corners add friendliness -- use sparingly (one curve is the sweet spot). Props: `borderSides` (omit sides to prevent double-borders when stacking adjacent Frames), `roundedCorners`, `borderWidth` (`border-2` | `border-4`), `interactive` (responds to Button hover via CSS custom properties).
- **Accent** (`components/Accent/Accent.tsx`): Gradient bar placed alongside a Frame to signal interactivity. Draws the user's eye to interactive elements using immediate, unconscious visual processing. Gradients: `magenta-green`, `purple-orange`, `orange-purple`. Props: `direction` (`vertical` | `horizontal`), `gradient`, `borderSides` (match adjacent Frame to avoid double-borders), `interactive`.
- **Button** (`components/Button/Button.tsx`): Wraps a Frame (or Frame + Accent) to make it interactive. Sets CSS custom properties (`--button-border-color`, `--button-bg`, `--button-accent-from/to`) on hover/focus so child Frame/Accent respond (orange border, cyan background, shifted gradient).
- **Heading** (`components/Heading.tsx`): Semantic heading component (h1-h6). Predefined size/weight classes per level. Uses Recursive font.
- **Icon**: Icons from `@phosphor-icons/react`. Prefer the **fill** variant for the acid design aesthetic -- bold, solid shapes with strong silhouettes. Fall back to regular weight for secondary/supporting icons.
- **UIGrid** (`components/UIGrid/UIGrid.tsx`): Site-wide layout grid with square cells. Uses ResizeObserver to compute cell size so cells never stretch or squash. Use for LCARS-style panel positioning. Pair with **GridBlock** (`components/UIGrid/GridBlock.tsx`) for placement (col, row, colSpan, rowSpan). NOT for cube faces -- use FaceGrid for those.

### Molecules (combinations of atoms)

- **NavLink** (`components/Nav/NavLink.tsx`): Button wrapping two adjacent Frames -- one for the icon, one for the text label. Icon Frame has all 4 borders; text Frame omits the left border to butt against the icon (double-border prevention pattern).
- **Logo lockup** (`components/Logo/Logo.tsx`): Frame + Accent + Logomark. The logomark itself is a real 3D CSS cube showing the U/T/C grid patterns.

### Organisms (groups of molecules)

- **SiteHeader** (`components/SiteHeader/`): Responsive header with desktop and mobile variants. Mobile has a menu button + expandable MobileNavPanel.
- **MobileNavPanel** (`components/Nav/MobileNavPanel.tsx`): List of NavLinks with Accent bars.
- **Cube** (`components/Cube/Cube.tsx`): Interactive 3D CSS cube on the homepage. Auto-spins, drag-to-rotate, tap-to-navigate. Each face maps to a site section.

